cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with learning to generate the surface of 3D shapes, which is a problem in computer graphics and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with 3D shape representation and manipulation, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
